===Dietary sources===
Vitamin D is found in few dietary sources.<ref name="Holick_2006"/><ref name="Norman_2008"/><ref name="Holick_2007"/><ref name="Brown_2008"/> Sunlight exposure is the primary source of vitamin D for majority of people, other than supplements.<ref name="Calvo_2005"/>

====Vitamin D<sub>2</sub>====
{{Main|Ergocalciferol}}

[[Fungus]], from USDA nutrient database (per 100 g):<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nal.usda.gov/fnic/foodcomp/search/index.html |title=USDA nutrient database&nbsp;– ''use the keyword 'portabella' and then click submit''}}</ref>
* Mushrooms, [[Agaricus bisporus|portabella]], exposed to [[ultraviolet light]], raw: Vitamin D<sub>2</sub>: 11.2 μg (446 IU)
* Mushrooms, portabella, exposed to ultraviolet light, grilled: Vitamin D<sub>2</sub>: 13.1 μg (524 IU)
* Mushrooms, [[shiitake]], dried: Vitamin D<sub>2</sub>: 3.9 μg (154 IU)
* Mushrooms, shiitake, raw: Vitamin D<sub>2</sub>: 0.4 μg (18 IU)
